headline.main: OUR BOMBERS HIT 2 SHIPS AT KISKA; Unscathed in This Raid, but in One Earlier Same Night We Lost Bomber, 2 P-38s ZERO IS BAGGED IN BATTLE In Solomons, Munda Is Raided Again -- Guadalcanal Patrols Kill Twenty Japanese

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON, Jan. 1 -- American pilots raided the Japanese at Kiska Island twice during the night of Wednesday-Thursday and made direct hits with several bombs on two Japanese cargo ships or transports lying in the harbor, but lost two fighters and one bomber.
abstract: Alaska: US pilots raid Kiska Is twice; hit 2 Jap cargo ships; lose bomber
